Sentencas: In this study, we fabricated highly efficient triple-conducting composite oxides using single- and double-layered perovskites.
Titulo: A highly efficient composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared to the cell performance of single- and double-layered perovskites, these triple-conducting composite oxides have better oxygen reduction capabilities and a robust structure showing a peak power density of 1.57 W cm(-2) and an ASR of 0.021 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C. No phase reactions or structural changes were found between the Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) and the SmBaCo2O5+delta (SBC) composites, as detected through in-situ high temperature X-ray diffraction (XRD) and high resolution transmission electron microscopy (HR-TEM) techniques.
Titulo: A highly efficient composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
